reviews.review: This was better than the previous two installments but still a bad movie. It had a cartoon/animated feel. It patched together a story relying heavily on the nostalgia of previous characters to fix a broken series. The movie jumps around too much, abandoning the original formula of a three act play. The characters have no real connection with the audience and basically I'm just happy it is over.

Don't care about the critics. Go see the movie with an open mind. The movie is not perfect and it has many flaws. If you stay away from the plot holes, this film has lot to offer for the fans. Every single character arc gets a satisfied conclusion and the performances were top notch especially Adam Driver and Daisy Ridley.
It's a cinematic masterpiece. Cinematography is amazing. Great twists and answered questions. Critics are insane
I enjoyed this film as well as the last 3. Is this one of the best, no. But it's close. It's have some flaws, but the overall the film is enjoyable.
Excellent movie. Great action scenes. Great plot. But the movie is frenetic, there is no time to admire it. If it was longer it would be a lot better.
Some great nostalgic moments and fun payoffs. Left me wanting a bit more but had a blast!

Loved it. For a film that could never satisfy every audience, this did a fantastic job. So glad it gave a final nod to a more holistic view of the Jedi and the previously established lore. The main characters are amazing and the portrayals so well acted. I couldn’t have hoped for more, and didn’t mind the homage to the fans— why wouldn’t a film give its fans a service at the end of a 9 part series? Well done, JJ.
I got exactly what I’d hoped from Abrams: Not an extremely well crafted film, but absolutely a fitting farewell to the characters we’ve loved for over four decades.

One movie with many movies in it. One Movie, 100 plot holes. 

JJ A, director of the 7th and 9th episode of StarWars, tried to please every fan but failed greatly. This movie is an overloaded and fragmented film that does not know what to say. At least we got some good pictures and a well done soundtrack. George Lucas Prequels are now officially gold standard compaired with this movie...
It was awesome, tied up unanswered questions well and was visually stunning , J.J. did a great job ending the saga.
